cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.SY, cs.PF 

This paper discusses a technique for saving energy in embedded DRAM caches, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and digital circuits (cs.DC). The technique involves dynamically reconfiguring the cache, which could also be considered as an approach for power management (cs.ET) and system optimization (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper evaluates the technique using benchmarks, which could be relevant to performance analysis (cs.PF).
